frameDefinitions: An Agent or Cause is responsible for placing a Valued_entity at risk.
The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .
An Agent causes a Patient to be more strong, often resulting in something that is more secure and safe.
An Agent affects an Artifact so that it is no longer capable of performing its inherent function.
An Asset is in a state where it is exposed to or otherwise liable to be affected by a Harmful_event, which may be metonymically evoked by reference to a Dangerous_entity.
frameExamples: His actions have <t>imperiled</t> his immortal soul!
The underwater sequences <t>warrant</t> the price of the admission alone.
Local Serbs are <t>strengthening</t> their grip on a narrow corridor along the Sava River between two large Serbian areas.
If you are a farmer, you are at <t>risk</t> for hearing loss caused by noise exposure in your work.
listRoleDefinitions: An (non-sentient) entity or state of affairs that leads to the peril to the Valued_entity.
The entity which may be negatively impacted as a result of the emperilment.
The sentient entity which causes the risk to the <fen>Valued_entity</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Valued_entity</fen> is put in danger.
The location where the <fen>Valued_entity</fen> is put in danger.
An Eventuality or an Entity that is taken to constitute sufficient reason for taking another <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that is taken to be justifiable given the <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that is being made stronger.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> makes the <fen>Patient</fen> stronger.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> fortifies the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The sentient entity causes the Artifact to not function.
The device that no longer works.
An inanimate entity or force that renders the <fen>Artifact</fen> non-functional.
The time at which the event takes place.
The place at which the event takes place.
Something judged to be desirable or valuable which might be lost or damaged.
The time period during which the <fen>Asset</fen> enjoys  the specified level of security from a <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.

A particular location in which the <fen>Asset</fen> is secure. Frequently, it is to be inferred that the characteristics of the location protect the <fen>Asset</fen> from a potential <fen>Harmful_event</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>A heavy contact to the opponent 's face</fex> may not merit just a verbal warning
There is a locked padlock that guarantees <fex>the information</fex> is secure.

Israel is insecure <fex>today</fex> not because it does
not have enough military power.
Workers need to make sure their property is secure <fex>at work</fex>.
